https://prez.dev/description.@value: The overarching categorization of vocabularies prepared by the Geological Survey of Western Australia (GSWA).

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: Vocabularies related to the study, exploration for and exploitation of physical processes and natural concentrations of materials for the main purpose of power generation. Energy resources include (a) concentrations of solid and/or fluid, inorganic or fossilized organic materials naturally occurring on or in the Earth’s crust (e.g. non-renewable fossil fuels such as petroleum, and natural gases); (b) natural physical processes within the Earth’s crust, atmosphere and hydrosphere (i.e. renewable energy resources such as solar, wind, hydro, solar thermal, marine, geothermal) or human-controlled activities (e.g. bioenergy/biomass, energy storage); and (c) nuclear energy. Adapted from Glossary of geology (Neuendorf et. al., 2011, 5th edition revised).
